(208,208,15799,'In Afghanistan, government regulation and monitoring will be important to understand how so-called CSR of the tobacco industry aggravates the harms caused.','Afghanistan does not have a comprehensive Ban on tobacco sponsorships and so-called CSR.','This briefing is prepared by the Global Center for Good Governance in Tobacco Control (GGTC), a partner of STOP, with inputs on methodology from Kerstin Schotte and Vinayak Prasad from the World Health Organization (WHO), Thomas E. Novotny of San Diego State University, and John E. Schneider of Avalon Health Economics. With support from STOP partners. ',NULL,'2022-05-11 08:55:03','2022-05-17 10:35:25'),
